The paper focuses on the use of deep Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for license plate detection and recognition, which is a common application in computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the training and fine-tuning of the CNNs, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML), specifically deep learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the second most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of algorithms for accurate and efficient license plate detection and recognition, which could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (AI) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.AI and cs.IR are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the availability of the system through an API, which could fall under the category of multimedia (MM). Hence, cs.MM is also a possible sub-category.
